rougeL.description: ROUGE score focusing on longest common subsequence.

msttr-100.description: Mean Segmental Type-Token Ratio, a measure of lexical diversity.

mean_pred_length.description: Average length of a system output.

distinct-1.description: Ratio of distinct unigrams / total number of unigrams.

vocab_size-1.description: Number of distinct words used by the system.

unique-1.description: number of unigrams that only occur once in the whole data.

distinct-2.description: Ratio of distinct bigrams / total number of bigrams.

vocab_size-2.description: Number of distinct bigrams used by the system.

unique-2.description: Number of bigrams that only occur once in the whole data

cond_entropy-2.description: Language model style conditional entropy -- N-grams conditioned on N-1-grams.

distinct-3.description: Ratio of distinct trigrams / total number of trigrams.

vocab_size-3.description: Number of distinct trigrams used by the system.

unique-3.description: Number of trigrams that only occur once in the whole data.

cond_entropy-3.description: Language model style conditional entropy -- N-grams conditioned on N-1-grams

bertscore.description: A BERT-based similarity measure between reference and generation.

bleurt.description: A learned metric to measure semantic equivalence between reference and generation.

meteor.description: An advanced lexical similarity metric also including stemming and synonymy matching.
